{
  "title": "Observation → measurement",
  "notes": "Measurement branch of the Observation family. Stage 1 (`mapspec/views/Observation__measurement.view.json`) fans out one `staging.observation_coded` row per `Observation.code.coding[]`. Stage 2's shared resolve pass (`mapspec/etl/_resolve_observation.sql`) walks each coding `http://loinc.org` → LOINC (via `cm.fhir_system_to_omop_vocab`) → `vocab.concept` (source) → `Maps to` → `vocab.concept` (standard `S`), DISTINCT ON (id, std.concept_id), and routes by `std.domain_id`. Rows with `std_domain='Measurement'` are projected by `mapspec/etl/Observation__measurement.sql`.\n\nAll variants hold the carrier code constant — LOINC **2339-0 'Glucose [Mass/volume] in Blood'** (source concept_id 3000483; already standard, so std == src == 3000483, domain `Measurement`, verified in `vocab.concept`) — and the same Patient/Encounter, so each diff isolates exactly ONE input dimension: value+unit, then comparator, then referenceRange, then status, then value-presence.\n\nProjection (Observation__measurement.sql): `measurement_concept_id`=std (3000483); `measurement_source_value`=raw code '2339-0'; `measurement_source_concept_id`=src (3000483); `measurement_type_concept_id`=constant **32817 'EHR'**; `value_as_number`=valueQuantity.value; `unit_concept_id`=UCUM standard concept resolved from valueQuantity.code (**8840 'milligram per deciliter'** for 'mg/dL'); `unit_source_value`=valueQuantity.unit; `operator_concept_id` from valueQuantity.comparator via VALUES('<',4171756),('<=',4171754),('>=',4171755),('>',4172704); `range_low`/`range_high` from referenceRange.first().low/high.value; `measurement_date`/`_datetime`=effective.ofType(dateTime) cast `::date` / `::timestamp` (offset dropped, wall-clock kept); `visit_occurrence_id`=referenceToId(encounter); no performer ⇒ `provider_id` NULL.\n\nValue-presence WHERE in the resolve pass keeps the row only if `value_number|value_string|value_code|value_text` is non-NULL — a panel-parent Observation with no top-level value[x] is dropped (its data lives in the component family). Status WHERE drops `entered-in-error`/`cancelled`/`unknown`. Both negative cases ⇒ `omop: {}` (zero rows; measurement and every other target table asserted empty). The glucose+mg/dL happy path and its produced row are grounded in real Synthea `cdm_ours_fhir.measurement` output (3000483 / 32817 / 8840 / source '2339-0'); the comparator, referenceRange, entered-in-error and panel-parent variants are hand-constructed (Synthea emits none of them) and their expected rows are derived from the SQL + verified `vocab.concept` rows.",
